<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1033" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1033">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 892.001/81.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">King of Siam</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">President</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-02"><hi rend="italic">December 2,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Please accept my heartfelt thanks for the cordial felicitations and
                            assurances of friendship and good will on part of your Government and
                            people, which I highly value,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Vajiravudh.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>